              <Textbox Name="Textbox74">
                <rd:DefaultName>Textbox74</rd:DefaultName>
                <CanGrow>true</CanGrow>
                <KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether>
                <Paragraphs>
                  <Paragraph>
                    <TextRuns>
                      <TextRun>
                        <Value>1. The overall objective of the Performance Appraisal System (PAS) is to manage and improve organisationaland individual performance by enabling staff participation and involvement in planning, execution and evaluation of work performance and personal development.
2. The PAS is a component of Performance Management Process that integrates work planning, target setting, performance reporting and feedback.
3. This appraisal form (F1) will be completed by all Employees in KICD service. It is expected that both the Appraisees and the Supervisors will read Sections of KICD HR Policy and Procedure Manual, 2018 on performance managementand the steps for completing the performance appraisal form below prior to embarking on the actual appraisal.
4.This form is to be filled in triplicate and distributed after the evaluation process as follows: Original to the Appraisee's personal file; Duplicate to be retained at the Directorate/Department; and Triplicate to be retained by the Appraisee.
5. Positive/negative circumstances impacting on the staff performance and possible review of targets should be documented as "reasons for variance" during the performance period.</Value>
                        <Style />
                      </TextRun>
                    </TextRuns>
                    <Style />
                  </Paragraph>
                </Paragraphs>
                <Top>0.47222in</Top>
                <Left>0.11111in</Left>
                <Height>1.98611in</Height>
                <Width>7.72348in</Width>
                <ZIndex>1</ZIndex>
                <Style>
                  <Border>
                    <Style>None</Style>
                  </Border>
                  <PaddingLeft>2pt</PaddingLeft>
                  <PaddingRight>2pt</PaddingRight>
                  <PaddingTop>2pt</PaddingTop>
                  <PaddingBottom>2pt</PaddingBottom>
                </Style>
              </Textbox>
